	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Praetor urbanus? 76? On the possibility that the author of the Interdictum Salvianum, which regulated pledges by coloni, was a praetor urbanus of about 76, see B. W. Frier, TAPhA 113, 1983, 224, 229; ZRG 96, 1979, 204-228, esp. 220-223; and Landlords and Tenants in Imperial Rome 107, note 118.\n" .
